sql:
SELECT addr_begin, addr_end
FROM memory_mappings
WHERE is_executable = 1;

SELECT p.process_name, mu.memory_usage
FROM processes p
JOIN memory_usage mu ON p.id = mu.process_id;

SELECT collection_date 
FROM memory_usage 
WHERE memory_usage = (SELECT MAX(memory_usage) FROM memory_usage);

external_knowledge:
Processes triggering exceptions often require investigation and monitoring to ensure system stability; 
Memory usage information can be used to diagnose potential memory leaks or performance bottlenecks; 
Files associated with memory mappings can be crucial in understanding system resource utilization.

